          <h3>12. Brian Phillips said...</h3>
          <div class="body"><p>I&#8217;ve recently gotten hooked on Vim&#8217;s integration with ctags and cscope.  I&#8217;m not too experienced yet but the following macros are very powerful:</p>


	<ul>
	<li>&lt;ctrl>-] takes you straight to the definition of the method/function/type/class/struct/sub/whatever your cursor is on. </li>
		<li>&lt;ctrl>-\ + s shows you every usage of that same item in the codebase</li>
		<li>&lt;ctrl>-T takes you back to where you were before you jumped with either of the above</li>
	</ul></div>
        </div>
        
        <div id="comment-4998" class="comment">
