          <h3>99. Garry said...</h3>
          <div class="body"><p>Just found out something else cool.  If you read the docs for fuzzyfinder.vim, you will find some cool keystrokes (which in turn also work for fuzzyfinder_textmate).</p>


	<p>When you have the file you want selected, you can do:</p>


	<p><span class="caps">CTRL</span>-] &#8211; open in new tab.</p>


	<p><span class="caps">CTRL</span>-j &#8211; open in split window.</p>


	<p><span class="caps">CTRL</span>-k &#8211; open in vertical split window.</p>


	<p>I use tabs a <span class="caps">LOT</span>, so <span class="caps">CTRL</span>-] is <span class="caps">AWESOME</span>.</p></div>
