          <h3>110. Rich said...</h3>
          <div class="body"><p>I noticed that a few people above were asking for a set of Rails based Vim plugins/configurations.  I store my Vim config on github.  Here it is if anyone&#8217;s interested:</p>


	<p><a href="http://github.com/manalang/vim-config/tree/master">http://github.com/manalang/vim-config/tree/master</a></p>


	<p>It includes everything you need for Rails dev (JS, <span class="caps">HTML</span>, CSS included).  It also includes Jamis&#8217; supercool fuzzy_finder_textmate plugin.  Just do a:</p>


	<p>git clone git@github.com:manalang/vim-config.git</p>


	<p>Then:</p>


	<p>mv vim-config ~/.vim
mv ~/.vim/.vimrc ~/.vimrc</p>


	<p>Enjoy!</p></div>
