          <h3>147. Nathan Fisher said...</h3>
          <div class="body"><p>Hi Jamis,</p>


	<p>Just thought I&#8217;d throw my setup into the fray;</p>


	<ul>
	<li>project.vim: Has nice file filtering so you can include only the file types and folders you want.</li>
		<li>minibufexpl.vim: Shows the open files with buffer number.</li>
		<li>vcscommand.vim: <span class="caps">SVN</span>/GIT integration amongst others.</li>
		<li>rails.vim: Does it need an introduction?</li>
	</ul>


	<p>I&#8217;ve set my make program to rake and mapped tests to &#8221;;mt&#8221;.  I think I will have to sit down and look at your plugin for sure!</p>


	<p>Cheers,</p>


	<p>Nathan</p></div>
